1
00:00:00,729 --> 00:00:05,100
In my first years of trading, I used to change
strategies almost every day.

2
00:00:05,100 --> 00:00:07,690
I didn’t have a trading plan.

3
00:00:07,690 --> 00:00:10,299
If I saw a signal, I took it.

4
00:00:10,299 --> 00:00:15,949
Until I realized that when it comes to technical
trading, my job was to seek out only the high

5
00:00:15,949 --> 00:00:17,550
probability entries.

6
00:00:17,550 --> 00:00:23,160
Today I’ll show you an effective strategy
to increase the odds on your trades, using

7
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:29,550
VWAP and the simplest price pattern you could
find, the V top and V bottom formation.

8
00:00:29,550 --> 00:00:36,800
You know the drill, like, subscribe and stick
around for the full video.

9
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:43,469
V-bottom
The V-bottom appears when price momentum switches

10
00:00:43,469 --> 00:00:47,559
from aggressive selling to aggressive buying.

11
00:00:47,559 --> 00:00:51,250
This is a powerful bullish reversal pattern.

12
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:57,200
Because of the nature of the aggressive buying
that takes place when a market reverses direction,

13
00:00:57,200 --> 00:01:02,969
it can be intimidating to enter, after the
market increased already quite a bit.

14
00:01:02,969 --> 00:01:08,910
This market shows a picture-perfect V-bottom
at the end of a bearish trend.

15
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:15,090
Price traded lower into a bottom and immediately
reversed higher with a massive increase in

16
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:16,110
momentum.

17
00:01:16,110 --> 00:01:23,500
Let’s be clear: it is nearly impossible
to predict V-bottoms, we won’t try to anticipate

18
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,860
this swing low.

19
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:30,490
We’ll wait for price to break the neckline
of the pattern, meaning the previous swing

20
00:01:30,490 --> 00:01:33,380
high before the bottom.

21
00:01:33,380 --> 00:01:37,390
This is basically an interruption in the previous
downtrend.

22
00:01:37,390 --> 00:01:43,150
And then we plan to enter a long position
once price retests the neckline.

23
00:01:43,150 --> 00:01:50,590
But with several conformations, we’ll talk
about them in a few moments.

24
00:01:50,590 --> 00:01:56,630
V-top
The V-top pattern appears when price momentum

25
00:01:56,630 --> 00:02:01,060
switches from aggressive buying to aggressive
selling.

26
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:03,630
This is a bearish reversal pattern.

27
00:02:03,630 --> 00:02:11,470
In a V-top, price traded higher and reversed
lower with a massive increase in momentum.

28
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:16,219
There are many ways to trade the V-top, but
the most conservative way would be to wait

29
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:22,880
for a break and close below the neckline and
to attempt a short once price pulls back to

30
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:28,010
the neckline and gets rejected.

31
00:02:28,010 --> 00:02:33,849
AVWAP
Trading V tops and bottoms can be difficult

32
00:02:33,849 --> 00:02:40,189
because you’ll recognize the pattern once
price breaks above or below the neckline.

33
00:02:40,189 --> 00:02:45,790
And another problem is the fact you’ll see
this setup many times throughout the day.

34
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:52,040
I filter these signals using VWAP, because
on the VWAP line you won’t see changes in

35
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:55,499
length or timeframe — unlike moving averages.

36
00:02:55,499 --> 00:03:00,810
Well, VWAP eliminates the confusion regarding
time frames and settings.

37
00:03:00,810 --> 00:03:05,709
It doesn’t matter if you use a 1-minute
chart or an hourly chart.

38
00:03:05,709 --> 00:03:08,030
There is only one VWAP line.

39
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:13,220
Flipping between time frames won’t affect
VWAPs position.

40
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:19,079
VWAP acts like a magnet, either attracting
or repelling.

41
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:22,160
For this strategy, we’ll use Anchored VWAP.

42
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:28,099
Anchored VWAP will tell you the price at which
most traders are commonly positioned.

43
00:03:28,099 --> 00:03:38,159
We’ll apply it on the lowest low of a V-bottom
formation, and on the highest high of a V-top

44
00:03:38,159 --> 00:03:41,209
formation.

45
00:03:41,209 --> 00:03:47,790
By anchoring VWAP to these exact price locations,
you’ll find dynamic resistance and support

46
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:54,450
level.

47
00:03:54,450 --> 00:03:56,310
For a long signal:
1.

48
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:59,370
Market forms a V-bottom formation
2.

49
00:03:59,370 --> 00:04:02,519
The V-bottom should be at a new low point
in the market.

50
00:04:02,519 --> 00:04:07,730
Meaning you can’t trade the formation if
there are recent lows below it.

51
00:04:07,730 --> 00:04:08,730
3.

52
00:04:08,730 --> 00:04:13,830
After you identified the V-bottom, you anchor
the VWAP on the recent lowest low

53
00:04:13,830 --> 00:04:14,830
4.

54
00:04:14,830 --> 00:04:22,040
If the neckline, the static support, aligns
with the Anchored Vwap, acting a dynamic support,

55
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:30,790
you buy at the re-test of the neckline

56
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:32,640
For a short signal:
1.

57
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:35,570
Market forms a V-top formation
2.

58
00:04:35,570 --> 00:04:39,870
The V-top should be at a new high point in
the market.

59
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:44,190
So you can’t trade the formation if there
are recent highs above it.

60
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:45,190
3.

61
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:49,340
After you found the V-top, you anchor the
VWAP on the recent highest high

62
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:50,340
4.

63
00:04:50,340 --> 00:04:56,750
If the re-test of the neckline, the static
resistance, aligns with the Anchored Vwap,

64
00:04:56,750 --> 00:05:03,030
as dynamic resistance, you look to sell the
re-test of the neckline

65
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:07,160
We are trading Crude Oil on the 4-hour time
frame.

66
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:14,230
Price dropped into this low but reversed,
with momentum increasing on the way higher.

67
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:18,690
Observe that this is valid V bottom because
price made a new recent low.

68
00:05:18,690 --> 00:05:24,510
When you start seeing an increase in buying
pressure, observing the price action by using

69
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:26,600
different time-frames can be very helpful.

70
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:31,400
So let’s move to the M30 time frame.

71
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:34,680
The neckline of the pattern is evident now.

72
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:40,430
The conservative way to trade would be to
wait for a break and close above the neckline

73
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:49,030
and to attempt a long position once price
pulls back to the neckline and gets rejected.

74
00:05:49,030 --> 00:05:55,250
We have the breakout above the neckline, so
let’s add the Anchored VWAP, at the lowest

75
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:59,410
low of the formation.

76
00:05:59,410 --> 00:06:07,590
Now we just wait for a rejection of the Anchored
VWAP and neckline.

77
00:06:07,590 --> 00:06:09,960
Stop loss goes below VWAP.

78
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:14,180
And my target is the next swing high in the
price structure.

79
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:24,030
The minimum risk to reward ratio should be
at least 2.

80
00:06:24,030 --> 00:06:30,210
Another target can be set above the neckline,
equal to the distance measured from the low

81
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:42,190
of the pattern to the neckline high.

82
00:06:42,190 --> 00:06:45,190
We trade Apple on the H1 time frame.

83
00:06:45,190 --> 00:06:47,780
I spot a potential V-bottom here.

84
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:51,920
Price made a new low and momentum switched
to the upside.

85
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:56,010
Let’s move to a lower time frame, to time
our entry.

86
00:06:56,010 --> 00:06:57,920
Here’s the neckline.

87
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:04,520
We’ll wait for price to break this level
and then enter a long position once price

88
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,940
retests this area.

89
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:13,870
But before that, we anchor the VWAP to find
the confluence zone.

90
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:17,940
Here’s the signal.

91
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:24,990
I see a rejection of the breakout area, and
at the same time, a rejection of the VWAP.

92
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:27,650
Stop loss below the VWAP line.

93
00:07:27,650 --> 00:07:30,990
And we target this swing high in price structure.

94
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:37,800
A risk to reward ratio of around 4.

95
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:43,861
Now that price consolidated above this swing
high, we remove the risk from our trade, by

96
00:07:43,861 --> 00:07:46,090
moving our stop to breakeven.

97
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:47,090
 

98
00:07:47,090 --> 00:07:52,290
Let’s trade a V top formation.

99
00:07:52,290 --> 00:07:54,360
Pound dollar.

100
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:57,180
H4 time frame.

101
00:07:57,180 --> 00:08:02,310
Price traded higher and reversed with an obvious
increase in momentum.

102
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:08,310
Like I said before, it is nearly impossible
to predict V-tops, and will wait for price

103
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:10,620
to break the neckline of the pattern.

104
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:18,510
Now let’s anchor the VWAP, to find our dynamic
resistance area.

105
00:08:18,510 --> 00:08:23,380
Here is the signal.

106
00:08:23,380 --> 00:08:28,390
We have a pin bar, rejecting the VWAP, at
the re-test of the breakout.

107
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:33,260
3 factors indicating a possible down move.

108
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:38,009
Stop loss above the VWAP and above the high
of the pin bar.

109
00:08:38,009 --> 00:08:41,880
Our target is this major swing low.

110
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:48,170
If price breaks this minor swing low, I’ll
move my stop to breakeven.

111
00:08:48,170 --> 00:08:59,769
Ok, now we are in risk free trade.

112
00:08:59,769 --> 00:09:04,370
The main problem will be the fact that you’ll
probably see many signals.

113
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:10,160
Even with the breakout area and VWAP confluence,
you will have problems identifying the best

114
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:15,189
signals to trade, especially if you are in
your first years of trading.

115
00:09:15,189 --> 00:09:22,650
So my advice is to add another filter, just
to make sure your setup is indeed worth trading.

116
00:09:22,650 --> 00:09:26,260
My additional filter is the central pivot
point.

117
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:32,290
I want the pivot to offer an additional layer
of confluence.

118
00:09:32,290 --> 00:09:41,790
In this example, we see a steep decline followed
by a rally to reach the top of the pattern.

119
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:48,480
The neckline would be here, the first area
of static support.

120
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:55,870
After the breakout, we add the VWAP line,
this time dynamic support.

121
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:59,230
We add the daily central pivot point.

122
00:09:59,230 --> 00:10:02,930
The third area of support.

123
00:10:02,930 --> 00:10:06,019
I also see this downward trendline.

124
00:10:06,019 --> 00:10:08,270
Which was also broken.

125
00:10:08,270 --> 00:10:11,040
This is our 4th level of support.

126
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:16,970
Let’s move to M30 time frame to pinpoint
the entry.

127
00:10:16,970 --> 00:10:20,839
Here’s our signal.

128
00:10:20,839 --> 00:10:24,570
A pin bar rejecting the previous levels.

129
00:10:24,570 --> 00:10:29,740
This is our 5th indication that the market
wants to go higher.

130
00:10:29,740 --> 00:10:34,720
Stop loss placement, below VWAP and below
the central pivot point.

131
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:44,120
And we target this swing high, a risk to reward
ratio of 3.

132
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:50,550
As price broke this swing, we remove the risk
from the trade, we move our stop loss to our

133
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:57,070
entry point.

134
00:10:57,070 --> 00:11:01,129
We are looking at Exxon Mobil on M30 time
frame.

135
00:11:01,129 --> 00:11:07,160
Price was in an uptrend, made a last push
higher, above the previous swing high, but

136
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,809
immediately reversed lower.

137
00:11:09,809 --> 00:11:17,139
This looks like a liquidity clear-out, with
many orders above this area.

138
00:11:17,139 --> 00:11:22,649
After price closed below the neckline, we
need to wait for a pullback to the initial

139
00:11:22,649 --> 00:11:23,649
breakout zone.

140
00:11:23,649 --> 00:11:28,839
That’s the first resistance level.

141
00:11:28,839 --> 00:11:34,620
We add the Anchored VWAP, from the highest
high of the V top formation.

142
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:40,230
That’s our dynamic resistance, the second
component.

143
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:46,900
We add the daily central pivot, which aligns
with our previous resistance levels.

144
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:51,629
That’s the third layer.

145
00:11:51,629 --> 00:11:57,040
I also see this major trend line, broken to
the downside.

146
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:59,540
Now could potentially act as resistance.

147
00:11:59,540 --> 00:12:05,899
4 different elements which indicate a further
price decrease.

148
00:12:05,899 --> 00:12:15,959
This candlestick, with a long wick, rejecting
our area of interest, is the signal to short

149
00:12:15,959 --> 00:12:17,220
the market.

150
00:12:17,220 --> 00:12:23,920
I like to see either a pin bar, or a candlestick
with an evident wick, or an engulfing bar,

151
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:28,050
forming at the VWAP – pivot point area.

152
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:32,389
Stop loss is placed above the VWAP line and
above the pivot level.

153
00:12:32,389 --> 00:12:39,519
And we’ll take our profit at the next major
swing low in the price structure, which represents

154
00:12:39,519 --> 00:12:45,910
a risk to reward ratio of 6.

155
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:55,529
As we broke this swing low, now it’s the
perfect time to move the stop to breakeven.

156
00:12:55,529 --> 00:12:59,850
Again.

157
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:07,399
Price makes a last push higher, above the
previous swing high, and reversed lower.

158
00:13:07,399 --> 00:13:11,709
Another possible liquidity clear-out.

159
00:13:11,709 --> 00:13:18,040
Price closed below the neckline, which is
the first resistance level.

160
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:21,970
We anchor the VWAP, from this high.

161
00:13:21,970 --> 00:13:27,220
That’s our second resistance.

162
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:36,699
We add the daily central pivot, which is resistance
number 3.

163
00:13:36,699 --> 00:13:43,560
We also see a pin bar candlestick, with a
long wick, rejecting the value area, and this

164
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:46,029
is the signal to sell.

165
00:13:46,029 --> 00:13:48,930
Stop loss above the VWAP line.

166
00:13:48,930 --> 00:13:55,319
Take profit, as usual, either at a major swing
in the price structure, or you set a fixed

167
00:13:55,319 --> 00:16:03,449
risk to reward ratio.

168
00:16:03,449 --> 00:16:07,740
If you found value and learned something new,
leave us a like.

169
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:11,850
This way we’ll know if you'd like to see
more videos like this one.

170
00:16:11,850 --> 00:16:18,850
And check out our academy program if you want
to further level up your trading.

171
00:16:18,850 --> 00:16:19,410
Until next time.

